22/09/2006
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The UN war crimes tribunal will announce the sentence against former Bosnian Serb politician and Radovan Karadzic's right-hand man Momcilo Krajisnik on 27 September, according to a statement Thursday (21 September). Krajisnik is charged with genocide during the 1992-1995 conflict in BiH, when he held several key positions, including speaker of the Bosnian Serb assembly. Prosecutors are seeking a life sentence for him. 
Also Thursday, the Belgrade daily Vecernje Novosti reported that chief war crimes prosecutor Carla del Ponte will visit Serbia on 2 October. Discussions will focus on Serbia's action plan to catch war crimes fugitive Radko Mladic. (Vecernje Novosti - 22/09/06; RTRS, AFP - 21/09/06)
